challengeName: Appointment Booking App - Java REST API Part 2 F2F Challenge
detailedRequirements:
The primary task of this challenge is to implement set of REST API endpoints in Java.

You are provided with existing JAVA REST API and you will add endpoints to it.

The deliverable of the challenge are :

  • - Implement the REST API endpoints.

  • - API Postman file with sample calls.

  • - Database sql script and test data.

  • - Updated build and deploy scripts (if needed).

  • - Deployment and verification document.

Challenge Requirements

Database Tables

  1. - Branches

    1. - ID

    2. - Name

    3. - Pic

    4. - Location Long

    5. - Location Lat

    6. - Address (string)

    7. - Phone

  2. - BranchesAppointmentType

    1. - ID

    2. - branch_id

    3. - appointment_type (ENUM)

Technology Stack

  • - JDK 1.8 or later

  • - Gradle 2.3+

  • - Spring for REST web services.

  • - MySQL

  • - Spring 4+

  • - Tomcat 7

Table Definitions

Note that naming convention is incorrect, follow naming convention used in current solution.

  1. - Branch_Agents

    1. - ID

    2. - Agent_id

    3. - Appointmenttype_id

    4. - Branch_id

  2. - Agent

    1. - ID

    2. - Full Name

    3. - Pic

  3. - AppointmentType_Requirements

    1. - ID

    2. - Requirement_description

    3. - AppointmentType_id

  4. - Appointment

    1. - ID

    2. - BranchID

    3. - eyeKnowAllRequirementsFlag (true/false)

    4. - AgreedOnRequirementsProcessingFalse (true/false)

    5. - FirstName

    6. - LastName

    7. - Email

    8. - PhoneNumber

    9. - AppointmentType_id

    10. - Comments

    11. - sendNotifications (true/false)

    12. - commenicationChannel (SMS/Email)

  5. - AppointmentTime (every record is 15 minutes slot)

    1. - ID

    2. - AppointmentID

    3. - StartDate (dd-mm-yyyy hh:mm)

    4. - EndDate (dd-mm-yyyy hh:mm)

    5. - AgentID

API Endpoint requirements

  1. - List Appointment Types

    1. - Return list of apointment types.

    2. - Route : GET /appointments/type

    3. - Input parameters

      1. - none.

    4. - Logic

      1. - Return AppointmentType enum list in array.

    5. - Output in json format

      1. - Array of AppointmentType

  2. - List required documents for appointment type

    1. - Retrieves array of requirements for the passed appointment type.

    2. - Route : GET /appointments/type/:type/requirements

    3. - Input

      1. - :type : represents the appointment type.

    4. - Logic

      1. - Return array of AppointmentTypeRerquirements array.

    5. - Ouptut in json format

      1. - Array of AppointmentTypeRerquirements

  3. - Get Available agents

    1. - Search the branch calendar to find the available agents of a given branch/appointment type/date.

    2. - Route : Get /calendar/branch/:branchId/appointmentType/:type/date/:date

    3. - Input

      1. - branchId - the branch id

      2. - type : represents appointmentType enum

      3. - Date : represents date in format dd-mm-yyyy

    4. - Logic

      1. - The logic should return the 15 minutes slots that have no agents available in it.

      2. - You will join Appointment, AppointmentTime, and Agent tables, to get agents available grouped by 15 minutes (start/end) slots.

      3. - The item of each array should be in format :

        1. - Slot : HH:MM

        2. - Agents : array of agents.

    5. - Output

      1. - Array of available agents at given date grouped by 15 minutes slots.

  4. - POST /appointments

    1. - Store appointment record.

    2. - Input (in json)

      1. - I know all requirements flag (true/false)

      2. - I approve processing the docs flag (true/false)

      3. - First name

      4. - last name

      5. - email

      6. - phonenumber

      7. - dates (array of 15 minutes dates)

      8. - agentId

      9. - comments

      10. - .. anything else needed for Appointment and appointmentsTime table.

    3. - Logic

      1. - Validate input.

      2. - Validate the agent available at the selected appointment type of given branch at the given dates. Otherwise return error.

      3. - Create appointments entry and appointmentsTime entries.

    4. - Response

      1. - 200 OK with created objects in json format

General Note

  • - Provide Postman file with sample calls.

  • - Add logging, and error handling properly.

  • - Sensitive data should be configurable.

  • - Provide the database schema as DDL, and test data as insert statements.

Deliverable

  • - All source code and scripts that implement the above requirements.

  • - Detailed deployment guide.

  • - Verification document.
